Karana Server</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utigerheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigerheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/31/02 3:11:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=350.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need a suggestion for 1hs</span><hr size=1>   In my opinion, Useing a 1hs is not the way to go. Save, save and improve your 2 Handed weapon. Get at least a 30dmg 40 del or better 2hander. <br>
<br>
Baton of Faith ( blunt) 30 40,<br>
Velium Cladimore (slash) 30 40<br>
ACGS ( slash) 30 43 15wis 25mana<br>
Mithril 2hander 21 40 31% haste , makes it a 21 28 weapon with a 40del dmg bonus<br>
or one of them Velium War lances <br>
<br>
             All theses will outdmg your centi warspear.<br>
 and are sold pretty cheap. the Mith is about 500pp and the rest around 1k or up.<br>
<br>
             Only Use a 1 hander If you are fighting casters that CH or Gate, when you really need to Bash. All else its really not worth useing 1 Hand at all.<br>
<br>
             With the new Dmg bonus to 2handers added recently, its  really the way to go when fighting in any givin group. Keep you skill up in 1hand slash, you never know when if you come across a Uber 1hs will bounce your way. But until then try to improve your 2hand weapons whenever possible, Its Really the only way Paladins can dish out any Dmg to compare to the dual weilding classes.<br>
<br>
